    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of a dynasty that flourished in Java from about 750 to 850 CE, dating after the fall of the Funan kingdom of mainland Southeast Asia. The dynasty was marked by a great cultural renaissance associated with the introduction of Mahayana Buddhism; it attained a high level of artistic expression particularly in temples and monuments.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
